Day-13 Notes – Kubernetes Volume Practice (AWS Cluster)
1️⃣ Sabse pahle cluster check kiya

Maine AWS Kubernetes cluster me nodes aur pods check kiye.

kubectl get nodes
kubectl get pods

Isse pata chala ki cluster properly running hai.

2️⃣ MySQL Pod ke andar enter kiya
kubectl exec -it mysql-pod-name -- /bin/bash

Is command se pod ke container ke andar shell open ho gaya.

3️⃣ MySQL ko password se login kiya
mysql -u root -p

Phir MySQL password enter kiya.

4️⃣ Database create kiya
CREATE DATABASE testdb;

Database check kiya:

SHOW DATABASES;

Isse confirm hua ki database successfully create ho gaya.

5️⃣ Pod delete karke test kiya
kubectl delete pod mysql-pod-name

Kubernetes ne naya pod automatically create kar diya.

6️⃣ Dubara MySQL login kiya
kubectl exec -it mysql-pod-name -- /bin/bash
mysql -u root -p
SHOW DATABASES;

Agar pod same node par create hua, to database still available tha.

7️⃣ Observation

✔ Pod delete hua → data delete nahi hua
✔ Same node par naya pod → old database mil gaya
❌ Different node par pod → old data nahi mila (hostPath volume case)
